  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      DEXTENZA for the Treatment of Post-Surgical Pain and Inflammation Compared to Standard of
      Care Topical Cortico-steroid Treatment in Patients who Undergo Bilateral Pterygium Surgery
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In patients who undergo bilateral pterygium surgery, eyes will be randomized to receive
      either DEXTENZA at baseline, Month 1 and Month 2 or prednisolone x 3 months. Both eyes will
      receive antibiotic drops four times per day for two weeks and Maxitrol ointment at bedtime
      for two weeks following surgery.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
